qas.question: Classical musicians continued to use many instruments from what era?
The theorbo and what other Baroque instrument fell into disuse?
The Baroque violin became what modern instrument?
What did the Baroque trumpet become?

context: Classical musicians continued to use many of instruments from the <a0_0>Baroque<a0_0/> era, such as the cello, contrabass, recorder, trombone, timpani, fortepiano and organ. While some Baroque instruments fell into disuse (e.g., the theorbo and <a1_0>rackett<a1_0/>), many Baroque instruments were changed into the versions that are still in use today, such as the Baroque violin (which became <a2_0>the violin<a2_0/>), the Baroque oboe (which became the oboe) and the Baroque trumpet, which transitioned to <a3_0>the regular valved trumpet<a3_0/>.
